    "Three of Four American Air Bases in North Africa Now Operational By Elton C Fay SIDI SLIMANE French Moroco The United States could launch atomic bombers on a moments no tice from three of the four huge air fields it has constructed in North Africa since 1951 They arent all complete In fact one presently has only runways and parking areas and a start on housing and other buildings But if war came tomorrow they could be used as launching points for medium range jet bombers and oceanspan ning heavy bombers Work on the first of the bases started in the spring of 1951 It was a time of urgency lent by the Ko rean war and worry that it would spark a world conflict in which per imeter bases to strike back against Russian air attack would be im perative Congressional committees which investigated the projects sharply criticized the construction time table quality of the work and the cost A Senate subcommittee heard testi mony that the five bases and head quarters then planned might run to 240 million Cost Estimate Up Army engineers supervising con struction of the bases for the Air Force now estimate four bases and"
